Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{commented}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the #oven{} is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, finely crush the @hazelnuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{}. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2cm thick. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Crack the @egg{1} (see pantry for amount) into a #medium bowl{} and whisk. Put the @panko breadcrumbs{50%g}, hazelnuts, @dried rosemary{1%sachet} and the @salt{½%tsp} for the breadcrumbs (see pantry for amount) into another #bowl{}, then mix.

Dip the chicken into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to coat the bottom of the pan.

> You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan, and fry until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Once golden, transfer the chicken to a baking tray. Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Discard the oil from the #chicken pan{}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and return to medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot, add the garlic and fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{75%g} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for amount). Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and stir through the @hard Italian style cheese{20%g}(grated) until melted, ~{1%minute}.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove from the heat.

When everything's ready, reheat the sauce if needed.

Share the chicken schnitzels between your plates. Serve the roast potatoes and @baby leaf mix{20%g} alongside.

Spoon the creamy sauce over the chicken and drizzle the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} over the salad to finish. Enjoy!